      "text": "Getting Started"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Welcome to the documentation for Better Auth in Next.js. This guide will help you set up authentication quickly and securely."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "id": "installation",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Installation"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "bash",
      "code": "pnpm add better-auth"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "id": "quick-start",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Quick Start"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Import the package and use it in your Next.js project."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "js",
      "code": "import { AuthProvider } from 'better-auth'\n\nexport default function App() {\n  return <AuthProvider>...</AuthProvider>\n}"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "id": "api-reference",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "API Reference"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "id": "authentication",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Authentication"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Use the AuthProvider to wrap your application and provide authentication context."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "id": "users",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Users"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "You can access the current user via the useAuth hook."
